{
  "analysis": "The image and stdout are already exact, but stderr still mismatches: the original emits 600 `Progress: %.1f%` updates after `Rendering high-resolution image...`, each preceded by `\r`, with the final one followed by `\nRendering complete\n`. A Python verification confirmed `100.0*y/600.0` for y=0..599 matches all 600 original progress values. I will first inspect the current Progress line escaping in /app/mystery.c before editing, then rewrite the source cleanly with the verified progress loop and exact image algorithm. After that, I will compile with `gcc -static -o reversed mystery.c -lm`, run, and verify stdout/stderr/image byte-for-byte plus compressed source size.",
  "plan": "Inspect the current Progress line in /app/mystery.c. Then rewrite /app/mystery.c with the exact stderr progress loop (`\rProgress: %.1f%%` for y=0..599) and the existing verified image algorithm. Compile with the required command, run ./reversed and /app/mystery, diff stdout/stderr, cmp image.ppm to /tmp/original.ppm, and check gzipped source size. If all pass, the task is complete.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /app; grep -n 'Progress' mystery.c
",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat <<'EOF' > /app/mystery.c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <math.h>
typedef struct{float x,y,z;}V;
static V v(float x,float y,float z){V r={x,y,z};return r;}
static V a(V p,V q){return v(p.x+q.x,p.y+q.y,p.z+q.z);}
static V s(V p,float t){return v(p.x*t,p.y*t,p.z*t);}
static float d(V p,V q){return p.x*q.x+p.y*q.y+p.z*q.z;}
static V n(V p){return s(p,1/sqrtf(d(p,p)));}
static V cr(V p,V q){return v(p.y*q.z-p.z*q.y,p.z*q.x-p.x*q.z,p.x*q.y-p.y*q.x);}
static V tr(V o,V dir){
 float t=1e9;int h=0;V np=v(0,0,0);
 float tt=(-0.5f-o.y)/dir.y;
 if(tt>0.001f&&tt<t){t=tt;h=2;np=v(0,1,0);}
 V sp[2]={v(0.8f,1.5f,-4.5f),v(-0.8f,1.5f,-4.5f)};
 for(int i=0;i<2;i++){V c=sp[i];V oc=a(o,s(c,-1));float b=d(oc,dir),c1=d(oc,oc)-0.16f,q=b*b-c1;if(q>0){float r=-b-sqrtf(q);if(r>0.001f&&r<t){t=r;h=1;np=s(a(oc,s(dir,r)),2.5f);}}}
 if(!h){float p=-dir.y;return s(v(0.7f+0.3f*p,0.7f+0.3f*p,1.0f),0.9f+0.1f*p);}
 V p=a(o,s(dir,t));
 V lp=n(v(-p.x,0.5f-p.y,-5-p.z));
 float sh=fmaxf(0.1f,d(lp,np)*0.9f+0.1f);
 if(h==2){int c0=((int)floorf(p.x)+(int)floorf(p.z))&1;return s(v(c0?0.6f:0.2f,c0?0.6f:0.2f,c0?0.6f:0.2f),sh);}
 return s(v(0.7f,0.2f,0.1f),sh);
}
int main(){
 fprintf(stderr,"Creating high-resolution image: 800x600\n");
 fprintf(stderr,"This will be downsampled with ffmpeg after rendering\n");
 fprintf(stderr,"Rendering high-resolution image...\n");
 for(int y=0;y<600;y++)fprintf(stderr,"\rProgress: %.1f%%",100.0f*y/600.0f);
 fprintf(stderr,"\nRendering complete\n");
 FILE*f=fopen("image.ppm","w");
 fprintf(f,"P3\n800 600\n255\n");
 V cam=n(v(0,1,-5));
 V right=n(cr(cam,v(0,1,0)));
 V up=cr(right,cam);
 for(int y=0;y<600;y++){
  for(int x=0;x<800;x++){
   float u=((float)x/799.0f-0.5f)*2.6666667f,vy=((float)y/599.0f-0.5f)*1.33333337f;
   V dir=n(a(a(cam,s(right,u)),s(up,vy)));
   V c=tr(v(0,0,0),dir);
   fprintf(f,"%d %d %d\n",(int)(c.x*255.99f),(int)(c.y*255.99f),(int)(c.z*255.99f));
  }
 }
 fclose(f);
 fprintf(stderr,"Wrote image to image.ppm\n");
 fprintf(stderr,"Done.\n");
 return 0;
}
EOF
",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /app; rm -f reversed image.ppm; gcc -static -o reversed mystery.c -lm && ./reversed >/tmp/cand_stdout.txt 2>/tmp/cand_stderr.txt; echo "reversed_exit=$?"; /app/mystery >/tmp/orig_stdout.txt 2>/tmp/orig_stderr.txt; echo "mystery_exit=$?"; diff /tmp/orig_stdout.txt /tmp/cand_stdout.txt && echo "stdout_match"; diff /tmp/orig_stderr.txt /tmp/cand_stderr.txt && echo "stderr_match"; cmp /tmp/original.ppm image.ppm && echo "IMAGE_EXACT_MATCH" || echo "IMAGE_MISMATCH"; md5sum image.ppm /tmp/original.ppm; echo -n 'source_gzip_bytes='; cat mystery.c | gzip | wc -c
",
      "duration": 1.0
    }
  ]
}
